# anythingllm-docker generated sites
#
# Each `sites/<domain>/` is a real deployment instance. The terraform state,
# real tfvars, generated `.env` (none should exist — we use Infisical), and
# any DOKS migration backup tarballs MUST NEVER be committed.

# Terraform state (the .terraform/ provider cache is per-checkout; tfstate
# contains droplet IPs + resource IDs and must stay out of git).
# .terraform.lock.hcl IS intentionally tracked — committing the lock file
# keeps provider versions reproducible across machines and CI runs.
**/terraform/.terraform/
**/terraform/*.tfstate
**/terraform/*.tfstate.*
**/terraform/*.tfstate.backup

# Real tfvars (only `*.example` is tracked)
**/terraform/terraform.tfvars
**/terraform/*.auto.tfvars

# Backup tarballs (never tracked — should live on the droplet or in DO Spaces)
**/backups/

# Local-only env (we shouldn't have these; Infisical injects at runtime)
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.prod

# Editor scratch
.DS_Store

# OpenTofu saved plans (contain sensitive values in plaintext) — never commit
**/terraform/*.tfplan
